2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 174
BY REPRESENTATIVE OWEN
DRUGS/TESTING: Requests the state surgeon general and the Louisiana Department of
Health to assess the feasibility of advancing fenbendazole for potential human use
in cancer treatment and to provide guidance on engaging federal authorities for
expedited evaluation while protecting public health
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the surgeon general and the Louisiana Department of Health to conduct
3 a professional assessment of fenbendazole as a potential treatment for cancer or other
4 medical conditions, to evaluate state-level options for supporting further review, and
5 to develop guidance on engaging the United States Food and Drug Administration
6 for compassionate use, expanded access programs, or prioritized clinical trials, while
7 maintaining rigorous patient safety and evidence-based standards.
8 WHEREAS, there is growing public interest in fenbendazole, a veterinary
9 anthelmintic drug, due to an increasing number of anecdotal reports and patient testimonials
10 from across the United States, including Louisiana, describing significant recoveries or
11 remissions from various types of cancer after self-administration, often in conjunction with
12 other therapies; and
13 WHEREAS, preclinical studies have indicated that fenbendazole may possess
14 anti-tumor properties, such as disrupting microtubules in cancer cells and inhibiting tumor
15 growth in laboratory models; and
16 WHEREAS, despite these preliminary findings, fenbendazole is not currently
17 approved by the United States Food and Drug Administration for human use, and clinical
18 evidence in humans remains limited to case reports and observational data without
19 large-scale randomized controlled trials; and
